		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Indie games* rarely get a disc release because of all the overhead involved. <a href="https://www.engadget.com/2017/11/13/esrb-indie-games-physical-boxed-edition-limited-run-special-reserve/" class="postlink">It may become even less common with ESRB changing its rate structure recently</a>. This doesn't affect people who play only AAA games, but I imagine that most people interested in both NESdev and modern consoles are also interested in playing indie games on modern consoles.<br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: 85%; line-height: normal">* Using <a href="http://slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=7603483&amp;cid=49985593" class="postlink">ceoyoyo's definition</a>: financed by an entity too small for venture capital.</span>

		

